    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi all. You've got me a little worried with all of this - I'm building a merchant terminal which is going to be used mainly for small transactions (few dollars max, like coffees etc.) Are you saying I can't let my customers walk out of the door for 10-60 minutes after purchasing? Or is it still safe to accept 0-conf transactions for small amounts? If so, what checking do I need to implement to rule out obvious double-spends and other cheats? Any links to detailed discussions would be very welcome.\n",
